criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Patients with severe intrauterine adhesions or scar the endometrium for whom drugs and surgical interventions were ineffective;
2. Age: 20-45 years old;
3. Who is willing to accept follow-up

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1.Chromosome karyotype abnormalities;
2.Severe congenital uterine malformations;
3.Severe endometriosis;
4.Severe adenomyosis;
5.Contraindications to pregnancy;
6.Contraindications to bone marrow collection;
7.Contraindications to hormone replacement therapy;
8.Medical history of pelvic tumors or receiving pelvic radiotherapy;
9.Unable to adhere to the hospital examination and follow-up, or carrying on other treatment during follow-up period.
